      public static <E> Set<E> getSet(Class<? extends Set<E>> setType, Collection<? extends E> content) throws SecurityException, NoSuchMethodException, IllegalArgumentException, InstantiationException, IllegalAccessException, InvocationTargetException
      Factory to create a new set based on required type and an optional content
      Type Parameters:
      E - The type of content for the created set
      Parameters:
      setType - type of set to create: either ArraySet or ...
      content - the optional content to add to the created set.
      Returns:
      a new set of the required type and content
      Throws:
      SecurityException - if the security manager doesn't allow access to the required constructor
      NoSuchMethodException - if the required constructor doesn't exit
      IllegalArgumentException - if the number of arguments provided to the constructor is wrong
      InstantiationException - if the required class is abstract
      IllegalAccessException - if the required constructor is inaccessible
      InvocationTargetException - if the invoked constructor raises an exception
